  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\nforge 0.2.0 (160cc81 2022-07-22T00:04:32.424398Z)\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge script\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\nmacOS (Intel)\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nSample code:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract Deployer is Script {\r\n  Contract contract = Contract(vm.envAddress(\"CONTRACT_ADDRESS\"));\r\n\r\n  function run() public {\r\n    // never gets here.\r\n  }\r\n\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWill result in:\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  couldn't deploy: Execution { reverted: true, reason: \"environment variable not found\", ....\r\nLocation: cli/src/cmd/forge/script/runner.rs:66\r\n\r\nThis is a bug. Consider reporting it at https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere was an easy workaround which is to just ensure everything gets initialized in the setUp function, but reporting because of the bug/crash!",
